post partum need advise okay so my baby is a week old and i have found myself at least once a day just breaking down into tears for no apparent reason and to make matters worse my husband is leaving for auto training for nine months in december i dont know how to deal with my emotions or why i keep breaking down has anyone else felt this way any ideas on how to deal with it alot of women go through a 'low' period right after having a baby it can be very confusing as you are always told this will be the greatest time of your life and you have a newborn child so feeling down in itself seems crazy right wrong the way you feel is completely normal you have a huge amount of hormones running through your body at the moment your milk will have come in and combined with sleep deprivation all in all your body is working overtime just to keep you running it sounds really hard but you need to take very good care of yourself in this time until your partner goes away you need to nap as much as possible while the baby does and eat as healthily as possible also do some things you weren't able to do whilst very pregnant get your hair done get a wax or a massage hope you feel better soon Breastfeeding Childbirth Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Guinea pig EastEnders Abortion debate Prostate cancer Androgen insensitivity syndrome Jon Secada Hypoglycemia Urinary incontinence Social rule Dog Infantilism Fertility awareness Kodocha Postpartum depression Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Elephant Sleep Humphrey Bogart Days of our Lives Milk Tupac Shakur Dieting Transsexuality One Tree Hill (TV series) Infant Madonna (entertainer) Theory of conduct Miss Saigon One Life to Live Melanie Wilkes Knots Landing Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Friends Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Grief Puberty John Sheridan (Babylon 5) Narcolepsy Miscarriage The Death Gate Cycle Insulin Acne Atomic Kitten Stomach cancer Sin City Cytomegalovirus Poker jargon The Amber Spyglass Scientology bel